Bike Sharing Assignment¶

05- 01- 2022¶

Business Goal: We are required to model the demand for shared bikes with the available independent variables. It will be used by the management to understand how exactly the demands vary with different features. They can accordingly manipulate the business strategy to meet the demand levels and meet the customer's expectations. Further, the model will be a good way for management to understand the demand dynamics of a new market.

Label/Target Column - cnt

DATA CLEANING¶

Dropping the irrelevant columns¶

In [9]:
#Dropping columns that are not relevant for analysis
bikes_df.drop(['instant','dteday'],axis=1,inplace=True)
  • instant is only row counter that is not useful for the data anaylsis .
  • dteday becomes irrelevant column as date can be derived from weekday,mnthand year columns.
In [10]:
#Also droppping  'casual' and 'registered' columns also
bikes_df.drop(['casual','registered'],axis=1,inplace=True)
  • casual and registered becomes irrelevant column as the target column cnt indicates the total number of bike rentals which includes both casual and registered

EDA¶

CONVERSION AND MAPPING¶

In [13]:
#Mapping season column to their values using season_map function

def season_map(s):
    return s.map({1:"spring",2:"summer",3:"fall",4:"winter"})

bikes_df[['season']]= bikes_df[['season']].apply(season_map)
In [14]:
#Mapping weathersit column to their values using weathersit_map function

def weathersit_map(ws):
    return ws.map({1:"Clear_Partly cloudy",2:"Mist_cloudy",3:"Light rain_Thunderstorm",4:'Heavy Rain_Ice Pallets'})

bikes_df[['weathersit']] = bikes_df[['weathersit']].apply(weathersit_map)
In [15]:
#Mapping month column to their values using month_map function

def month_map(m):
    return m.map({1:'Jan', 2:'Feb', 3:'Mar', 4:'Apr', 5:'May', 6:'Jun', 7:'Jul', 8:'Aug', 9:'Sep', 10:'Oct', 11:'Nov', 12:'Dec'})

bikes_df[['mnth']] = bikes_df[['mnth']].apply(month_map)
In [16]:
#Mapping weekday column to their values using weekday_map function

def weekday_map(w):
    return w.map({0:"Sunday",1:"Monday",2:"Tuesday",3:"Wednesday",4:"Thursday",5:"Friday",6:"Saturday"})

bikes_df[['weekday']] = bikes_df[['weekday']].apply(weekday_map)

In [18]:
#Creating Categorical_plot function for plotting cnt(Dependent Variable) VS other columns(Independent Variable)
sns.set_style("darkgrid")
def Categorical_plot(col_name):
    plt.figure(figsize=(15, 10))
    plt.subplot(2,1,1)
    sns.boxplot(x = col_name, y = 'cnt', data = bikes_df)
    plt.subplot(2,1,2)
    sns.barplot(x= col_name, y='cnt', data=bikes_df)
    plt.show()

Inferences

  • temp and atemp follow similar relation pattern with cnt variable

  • count of total rental bikes is observed higher for high humidity values
  • count of total rental bikes is inversely proportional to windspeed variable.

Model Building¶

In [45]:
#Creating build_model function which will return lm and X_train_rfe values

def build_model(X_train_rfe):
   
    X_train_rfe1 = sm.add_constant(X_train_rfe) # Adding a constant variable 
    lm = sm.OLS(y_train,X_train_rfe1).fit()
    X_train_sm = sm.add_constant(X_train_rfe)
    lm = sm.OLS(y_train, X_train_sm).fit()
    return lm,X_train_rfe1
In [46]:
#Creating check_vif function which will return vif values

def check_vif(X_train_rfe):
    vif = pd.DataFrame()
    X = X_train_rfe
    vif['Features'] = X.columns
    vif['VIF'] = [variance_inflation_factor(X.values, i) for i in range(X.shape[1])]
    vif['VIF'] = round(vif['VIF'], 2)
    vif = vif.sort_values(by = "VIF", ascending = False)
    return vif

So, the equation of our best fitted line is

Equation¶

cnt = (0.2349 yr) - (0.0851 holiday) + (0.4432 atemp) - (0.1493 windspeed) + (0.0723 season_summer) + (0.1244 season_winter) + (0.0580 mnth_Aug) - (0.0585 mnth_Dec) - (0.0565 mnth_Feb) - (0.0875 mnth_Jan) - (0.0442 mnth_Nov) + (0.1044 mnth_Sep) - (0.2875 weathersit_Light rain_Thunderstorm) - (0.0828 weathersit_Mist_cloudy) + 0.2114

Observation¶

count of total rental bikes is dependent mainly on below features:¶

  • year
  • holiday
  • Temperature(atemp)
  • windspeed
  • Season: season_summer,season_winter
  • Month: mnth_Aug, mnth_Dec,mnth_Feb,mnth_Jan,mnth_Nov,mnth_Sep
  • weathersit: weathersit_Light rain_Thunderstorm, weathersit_Mist_cloudy

count of total rental bikes increases with increase in below features(Directly-proportional):¶

  • year
  • Temperature(atemp)
  • Season: season_summer,season_winter
  • Month: mnth_Aug,mnth_Sep
  • weathersit: weathersit_Light rain_Thunderstorm, weathersit_Mist_cloudy

count of total rental bikes decreases with increase in below features(Inversely-proportional):¶

  • holiday
  • windspeed
  • Month: mnth_Dec,mnth_Feb,mnth_Jan,mnth_Nov
  • weathersit: weathersit_Light rain_Thunderstorm, weathersit_Mist_cloudy
In [ ]:
